04/03/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Mladen Drljac, 50, was arrested on Monday (March 3rd) for suspected war crimes committed in the Bosnaska Krupa municipality in 1992. 
Officers of the BiH State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) detained him in Banja Luka. 
Last Thursday, they arrested Bosnian Serb Jovan Ostojic, 53, who commanded the 11th infantry unit of the Bosnian Serb army. 
He is blamed for the arrest, torture and alleged murder of 36 Bosniaks from Bosnaska Krupa between July 1992 and May 1995. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 04/03/08; RTRS, Fena - 03/03/08)
